<br>
Since coming to FV this year, I have played two female characters (one beautiful and one scaly and ugly) and am seriously considering re-rolling as a male. <br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
I expected male characters to instigate a certain amount of flirting because after all this is an RP server and sex drives are conceivably a part of our characters. But the flirtation I have experienced has escalated to the point of harassment.<br>
<br>
I have found a lot of the guys I encounter to be desperately lonely men / boys who want to pursue romantic relationships beyond the boundaries of EQ. It has gotten to the point that I cannot log on without receiving at least 3 – 4 tells from men / boys who make me decidedly uncomfortable on a RL level.<br>
<br>
I am not playing EQ to be anyone’s girlfriend, wife, or mother and I am tired of dealing with the torrent of unwanted advances and RL sob stories. EQ is supposed to be an outlet for me to relax and have fun – unfortunately, it seems I cannot do those things as a female Avatar.<br>
<br>
To any men who read this, please think about this when pursuing females characters. Keep your RL out of it and if someone doesn’t reciprocate your in game love interest, just drop it. Women get harassed enough in RL without having to come online and deal with it to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utherisiamorningdewfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TherisiaMorningdewFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ambition Starts Early</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 3:22:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaolla-su.net/~shinobu/shinchan8.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Lol</span><hr size=1> You think that's bad, try being in the same situation as a guy playing a girl.<br>
