<br>
I don't play a female to get gifts or any special attention from male characters, I choose my characters sex based on RP reasons.  If I have a backstory that works better or would be more fun to play as a female, then so be it, otherwise I default to a male character.<br>
<br>
So far I have three female and three male characters created and active on different servers, and on this server I have been male 3 times and female twice.  /sigh rerollitis.<br>
<br>
Sylvinea is a recreation of my first serious EQ character.  I loved roleplaying her (had some great storylines going as well) but she was on the Brell server, and while it was supposed to be the &quot;unofficial double secret roleplay server&quot;  by the time I reached the mid to high levels d00ds had taken over, I was disillusioned with EQ, and it was getting harder to group with my friends in Evoluxa and other RP'ers cause I am one of the slowest levelers in the world at times.  Here on FV with like minded people, I really want to see how her story unfolds<br>
<br>
Hmmm.  Is there a point floating around here.  Ahh, yes.<br>
<br>
I play a female because Sylvinea IS a female. Those that know me in game ooc know that PoSylvinea is a man.  I enjoy roleplaying characters as different from myself as possible, after all, isn't the point of roleplay to become someone else, for a certain time?<br>
