You should pretty much assume anything you &quot;know&quot; about someone on-line is BS until proven otherwise.<br>
<br>
Jaded?  Perhaps.. but if it means that much to you weather the person your talking to is male or female.. then save yourself the hassel and just assume they're all fellows.<br>
<br>
It shouldn't matter if you're roleplaying... that should be interaction with the persona, not the person behind it.  (That's a shallow view, everyone puts themselves into whatever they play... but I hope you know what I mean.)<br>
<br>
My first &quot;serious&quot; character was a female woodelf.. this was back in the days of yonder when woodelf males were cursed with that.. freaking.. pine.. tree.. on their chest.  I hated it, thusly made a woman.<br>
<br>
Yup, people hit on me.  I let them know politely I was a fella' and not really interested, but thanks.  Most acted like adults, &quot;Oh so sorry lol&quot; that sort of thing.  Some kids reacted poorly... had one that said I was lying :/<br>
<br>
Anyway, all my other characters have been male.  For me, it was more of a graphic thing.  I cant stand having a character that looks aweful.  <br>
<br>
I write alot, and if a female character ever leaps into my mind that I want to play... I'd play it.  Dont really care if other people approve or not, I play for my own enjoyment first.. and everyone's entertainment second <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for hitting on females... yeah there are some pretty crummy people out there.  I play with my girlfriend often, and some of the things people say and do are just plain rude.  I wish this game was rated mature... maybe that would help some.  <br>
